    Works great - with some tweaking

Reviewed in the United States on April 20, 2021Style: PodMaster D USBVerified Purchase









    I'm using the heck out of this mic! It's a great buy. It sounds warm and delightful, and it's not terribly sensitive to plosives. Plug it in and it works.Kind of.If you're using it on Windows 10, the output is VERY low. Low enough that you'll want to crank the Volume control on the mic and boost it in your recording software just to get an audible signal. Unfortunately, that will raise a TON of noise.You'll need to download a preamp app to get a signal out of it you can work with. The good news is you can find good free preamp apps, and once you set them they just WORK, no matter what other apps you're running to record. The bad news is you'll have to play around with it until you achieve a balance between the mic's Volume control and the gain controls in the preamp software to get a clean signal. That took me quite a lot of time.TL;DR: It's a great mic, but it is most definitely NOT plug and play.

